summary: Ben Rice, a rookie for the New York Yankees, achieved a remarkable feat by becoming the first player in franchise history to hit three home runs in a single game. The impressive feat has drawn attention from various news outlets, including ESPN, Boston 25 News, CBS Sports, and Bleacher Report. Rice, a former Dartmouth University player, has quickly made a name for himself with the Yankees, showcasing his power and potential in his debut season.

name: Djokovic
summary: Novak Djokovic made a successful return to Wimbledon, winning his first match despite undergoing knee surgery just weeks prior. His dominant performance comes as he aims to break Federer's Grand Slam record. The 2024 Wimbledon tournament is underway, featuring Djokovic and Ons Jabeur among the top players. Djokovic has found a loophole in the tournament's all-white dress code, sparking discussion. Despite his recent injury, Djokovic remains a contender for an eighth Wimbledon title, while Iga Swiatek hopes to excel on grass. Before his Wimbledon match, Djokovic praised his opponent, Holger Rune. During his match, the crowd erupted in support when England won in the Euro 2024 tournament. Djokovic's wife, Jelena, plays a significant role in his life and career.
